            <h2 class="cursive-accent">what i've been working on</h2>
            <h1>al-muslim</h1>

            <div class="product-hero mt-xl">
                <div class="product-logo-container">
                    <img src="Screenshot 2025-11-27 214334.png" alt="al-muslim logo" class="product-logo">
                </div>
                <div class="organized-content">
                    <div class="detail-block">
                        <h4>the project</h4>
                        <p>
                            i started al-muslim because most apps out there felt too busy.
                            i wanted something quiet, accurate, and completely private.
                            it's built for those who value focus over features.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="grid mt-xl"
                style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: var(--space-lg);">
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="text-red ui-font">01</span>
                    <h3>real-time prayer</h3>
                    <p>
                        handles all the math locally. your location never leaves your phone.
                        accurate schedules, no matter where you are.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="text-red ui-font">02</span>
                    <h3>clean quran</h3>
                    <p>
                        no distractions. just high-contrast text and a fast search
                        engine. built for reading, not for clicking through ads.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="text-red ui-font">03</span>
                    <h3>adhkar & qibla</h3>
                    <p>
                        essential tools for the daily routine. a simple compass
                        and a list of adhkar that stays out of your way.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="text-red ui-font">04</span>
                    <h3>multi-arch</h3>
                    <p>
                        available on android right now. i'm testing desktop builds
                        for windows and linux. ios is on the roadmap.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="organized-specs mt-xxl">
                <h2 class="ui-font">the tech stack (for nerds)</h2>
                <ul class="detail-block" style="list-style: none;">
                    <li><strong>framework:</strong> react native + expo (smooth & native)</li>
                    <li><strong>database:</strong> sqlite (local-first, indexed)</li>
                    <li><strong>privacy:</strong> zero external telemetry</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

